  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Firming cooperative business diversification and member professionalization</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ABM laquo;Iterambere ryrsquo;Abahinzi-Borozi ba Makera raquo; is a maize and cooperative and started its activities in 2007. IABM has 799 members of whom 64.7% females and 35.3% males. Besides the current members IABM has 976 potential members (supplying maize and seeds to IABM). It is primarily engaged in seed Multiplication and maize processing into flour.Among other activities include the supply of production inputs (seeds  fertilizers and pesticides)  members training / capacity building  commercialization of maize flour  distribution animal feed from the maize factory  and support members to access bank loans.Apart from the maize value chain  IABM members are active horticulture value chain by producing different horticultural crops including but not limited to onions  tomatoes  sweet peppers  peas  cabbages. In 2020 Action Plan  Agriterra and IABM have agreed to extend the maize hybrid seed multiplication project by trying production of prebasic seeds  strengthening capacity of staff and members on maize seed processing mobilise more members into the cooperative introduce data management tool for member relationship management(CRM) conduct an external financial audit and develop a procurement manual. Besides this support  Agriterra will extend its advisory work into irrigation scheme operationalisation and management and taking record keeping at both farmer and cooperatives revel. Agriterra will also train IABM and its members on Marketing  Organic fertilizer making and composting. To foster financial solidity of IABM  Agriterra will give them a strategic financial management.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall goal of this project to strengthen the cooperatives business diversification and enhance member professionalization towards increased farmer revenue.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is in line with IABMs strategic plan where the cooperative aims to strengthen its business diversification and professionalization of its members. This project is composed of three main sections: Section one composed of activities to be implemented by the cooperative with advise of the Agriterra Buiness Advisor. These activities include: 1. Expanding training on hybrid seeds production and introduction of prebasic seeds  2.Technical support for cooperative staff and farmers on sorting  grading and packaging maize seeds  3.Participate in agricultural exhibition  Mobilize and train new members with special focus on youth  4.Purchase and introduce data management tool for member relationship management(CRM)  5.Conducting external audit for 2019  and 6. Develop a sound procurement manual.Section two composed of key advisory services of the business advisor towards the cooperative in line with its main goal. These include but not limited to : 1) Support institutionalisation of record keeping at farmer and cooperative level and 2) Advice on irrigation scheme managementSection three composed of key trainings that Agriterra will provide to IABM cooperative. These include: 1) Basic Marketing Training 2)Training on organic farming and composting workshop Strategic 3) Financial Management Training</narrative>
  </description>
